==College World Series==
{{Main article|1962 College World Series}}
The 1962 season marked the sixteenth NCAA Baseball Tournament, which culminated with the eight team [[College World Series]].  The College World Series was held in [[Omaha, Nebraska]].  The eight teams played a double-elimination format, with Michigan claiming their second championship with a 5–4, fifteen-inning win over Santa Clara in the final.<ref name=CWS />
{{:1962 College World Series}}

